Indicative Value: &#xA3;3.75M + &#xA3;0.75M VAT = &#xA3;4.5M

The proposed procurement route will be a two stage tender process, using the NEC4 ECC form of Contract, Option A Priced Contract with Activity Schedule.

Full details will be available in the selection questionnaire in the tender pack. https://procontract.due-north.com/Advert?advertId=3f5000db-dca8-ef11-8132-005056b64545

&quot;Grimsargh Skew Bridge is a single span reinforced concrete structure which was previously strengthened in 2001. Currently, the width of the main bridge restricts traffic to a single lane width, restricting flow of vehicles. There are steel pedestrian footbridges on both sides (east &amp; west) of the bridge. The eastern footbridge is relatively new and will be retained. A scheme has been developed to widen the structure to enable two-way traffic for vehicles and therefore improve traffic flows. The works substantially consist of the demolition of the western footbridge, the widening of the existing main bridge and the installation of a signalised pedestrian crossing to the north of the bridge, adjacent to the nearby primary school. 

The design of both the temporary and permanent works required for the bridge widening is proposed to be designed by the contractor to match the fixed highways alignment designed by LCC. 

The full scope of this project is contained at ITT Appendix 5 and the associated contractual documents. Please ensure that you read all documentation in the preparation of your Tender and should you have any queries on the contents, please raise a clarification request in the manner described at paragraph 2.7 within the timescales outlined with paragraph 3.1.&quot;

